						<div class="postbody">Looks awesome, but how does it work over time? The scanline and cycle options at the bottom don't really apply to this screen, since this is not a snapshot of a specific moment, but the log of an entire frame. Also, since it's nearly impossible to sync the CPU with the PPU in a game, those annotations may jitter a lot when the emulator is running. I guess it's possible to keep the CPU debugger open and advance frame by frame to see this window in &quot;slow motion&quot;, right?</div>

